H.B. 120
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF NORTH CAROLINA
Feb 13, 2025
SESSION 2025
HOUSE PRINCIPAL CLERK
H D
HOUSE BILL DRH40088-MGa-62
Short Title: Expand Project C.A.R.E./Funds. (Public)
Sponsors: Representative Moss.
Referred to:
1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT APPROPRIATING FUNDS TO THE DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH AND HUMAN
3 SERVICES, DIVISION OF AGING AND ADULT SERVICES, FOR EXPANSION OF
4 THE PROJECT CAREGIVER ALTERNATIVES TO RUNNING ON EMPTY (PROJECT
5 C.A.R.E.) PROGRAM.
6 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
7 SECTION 1. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the Department of
8 Health and Human Services, Division of Aging and Adult Services, the sum of one million forty
9 thousand five hundred fourteen dollars ($1,040,514) in recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal
10 year and the sum of one million forty thousand five hundred fourteen dollars ($1,040,514) in
11 recurring funds for the 2026-2027 fiscal year to expand the Project Caregiver Alternatives to
12 Running on Empty Program (Project C.A.R.E.), which provides support to family caregivers of
13 people living with Alzheimer's disease or other related dementias.
14 SECTION 2. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025.
*DRH40088-MGa-62*

